---
import Layout from "@/core/components/layout/main-layout.astro";

const metadata = {
    description:
        "Alexandre Trotel is a software builder focused on useful products, entrepreneurship, and technology.",
    title: "Alexandre Trotel",
};

const linkClass =
    "font-medium text-foreground decoration-border/80 decoration-[0.06em] underline underline-offset-[0.18em] transition-colors hover:text-muted-foreground";
---

<Layout title={metadata.title} description={metadata.description}>
    <section class="mx-auto flex h-full w-full max-w-[38rem] flex-col py-1">
        <div class="space-y-5">
            <h1
                class="font-sans text-[1.0625rem] leading-6 font-semibold text-foreground"
            >
                Alexandre Trotel
            </h1>
            <div
                class="space-y-3.5 text-[0.9375rem] leading-[1.85] text-muted-foreground"
            >
                <p>
                    I believe the world becomes clear through action, which is
                    why I constantly build, explore, and experiment.
                </p>
                <p>
                    I am the co-founder of <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://www.radion.app"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">Radion</a
                    >, where we turn prediction market activity into clear
                    market and trader intelligence. Our goal is to help traders
                    make better decisions with transparent data that is easy to
                    read.
                </p>
                <p>
                    I also run <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://www.zapstudio.dev"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">Zap Studio</a
                    >, a side project for type-safe TypeScript libraries that
                    work across stacks, so developers can move between tools
                    more easily.
                </p>
                <p>Through Zap Studio:</p>
                <ul
                    class="list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5 marker:text-muted-foreground"
                >
                    <li class="pl-1">
                        <a
                            class={linkClass}
                            href="https://jsr.io/@zap-studio/validation"
                            rel="noreferrer"
                            target="_blank">validation</a
                        > provides Standard Schema utilities and validation error
                        helpers.
                    </li>
                    <li class="pl-1">
                        <a
                            class={linkClass}
                            href="https://jsr.io/@zap-studio/fetch"
                            rel="noreferrer"
                            target="_blank">fetch</a
                        > is a type-safe fetch wrapper with Standard Schema validation.
                    </li>
                    <li class="pl-1">
                        <a
                            class={linkClass}
                            href="https://jsr.io/@zap-studio/permit"
                            rel="noreferrer"
                            target="_blank">permit</a
                        > is a type-safe authorization library for TypeScript with
                        Standard Schema support.
                    </li>
                    <li class="pl-1">
                        <a
                            class={linkClass}
                            href="https://jsr.io/@zap-studio/webhooks"
                            rel="noreferrer"
                            target="_blank">webhooks</a
                        > provides type-safe webhook routing with signature verification.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>I also maintain some tools under licenses like GPL-3.0:</p>
                <ul
                    class="list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5 marker:text-muted-foreground"
                >
                    <li class="pl-1">
                        <a
                            class={linkClass}
                            href="https://github.com/alexandretrotel/todo-tree"
                            rel="noreferrer"
                            target="_blank">todo-tree</a
                        > finds and displays TODO-style comments in your codebase.
                    </li>
                    <li class="pl-1">
                        <a
                            class={linkClass}
                            href="https://github.com/alexandretrotel/mntn"
                            rel="noreferrer"
                            target="_blank">mntn</a
                        > is a command-line tool to manage your dotfiles.
                    </li>
                    <li class="pl-1">
                        <a
                            class={linkClass}
                            href="https://github.com/alexandretrotel/feedyourai"
                            rel="noreferrer"
                            target="_blank">fyai</a
                        > combines text files for AI processing with filtering options.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    If you meet me, I could talk hours about <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_engineering"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">software engineering</a
                    >, <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alfred_Adler"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">Adlerian philosophy</a
                    >, <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">psychology</a
                    >, <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Startup_company"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">startups</a
                    >, <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">Bitcoin</a
                    >, <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Investment"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">investment</a
                    >, and <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Science"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">science</a
                    >, from <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quantum_physics"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">quantum physics</a
                    > to <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">astronomy</a
                    >. I feel like each of these topics help me to understand
                    how the universe works.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Finally, outside of code, I do music production (<a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Progressive_house"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">progressive house</a
                    >, <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Future_house"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">future house</a
                    >, <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bass_house"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">bass house</a
                    >, and <a
                        class={linkClass}
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Future_bass"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        target="_blank">future bass</a
                    >), watch anime, read books, and play badminton.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
